security_findings.evidence:
UNPATCHED FIPfOpenListNotifyConflictStart @0x1C0013D34 (root read used as-is; flag always 0):
    uint8_t flag = *(uint8_t*)(arg4 + 8) & 1;   // Encoded bit, always 0
    int64_t* root = *arg4;                       // read plainly
    // child pointers decoded only when flag is set (never here)

PATCHED FIPfOpenListNotifyConflictStart @0x1C0013D04 (root decode added, guard never satisfied):
    uint8_t flag = *(uint8_t*)(arg4 + 8);
    int64_t* root = *arg4;
    if ((flag & 1) && root) root ^= arg4;        // NEW; dead because flag == 0

The tree header is passed as arg1 to RtlRbInsertNodeEx (0x1C0013EEE / 0x1C0013ED9), confirming RTL_RB_TREE. The driver never stores to [tree+8]; the only store in the function is to the freshly allocated node (mov [rdi+18h], r9 at 0x1C0013E8F). Every caller zero-initializes its local tree (movdqu [P...], xmm0) and never sets the Encoded bit.
